text: is a Japanese football player. She played for the Japan national team. ==Biography== Tomari was born in Nagoya on March 26, 1990. After graduating from Osaka University of Health and Sport Sciences, she joined Urawa Reds in 2012. In 2015, she moved to AC Nagano Parceiro.AC Nagano Parceiro She played 61 matches and scored 19 goals. In 2018, she moved to Austrian Frauenliga club Wacker Innsbruck.AC Nagano Parceiro In 2019, she moved to German 2. Frauen- Bundesliga club Cloppenburg. In 2020, she returned to AC Nagano Parceiro.AC Nagano Parceiro On July 27, 2017, Tomari debuted for the Japan national team against Brazil.
